  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "OpenEXR security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for OpenEXR is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "OpenEXR is a high dynamic-range (HDR) image file format originally developed by Industrial Light \u0026 Magic for use in computer imaging applications.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nThere's a flaw in OpenEXR's rleUncompress functionality in versions prior to 3.0.5. An attacker who is able to submit a crafted file to an application linked with OpenEXR could cause an out-of-bounds read. The greatest risk from this flaw is to application availability.(CVE-2021-3605)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for OpenEXR is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "OpenEXR",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
